SIMPLE: tab
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tab
<hw>Tab</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Etymol. uncertain.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The flap or latchet of a shoe fastened with a string or
a buckle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A tag. See <er>Tag</er>, 2.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A loop for pulling or lifting something.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A border of lace or other material, worn on the
inner front edge of ladies' bonnets.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <def>A loose pendent part of a lady's garment; esp., one
of a series of pendent squares forming an edge or border.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>a small projecting piece of a file folder, file
card, or similar sheet used in a filing system, on which a notation is
written to permit convenient search for the folder, card, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>a bill or check for some purchase, as in a
restaurant; <as>as, the salesman will pick up the
<ex>tab</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>8.</sn> <def>a key on a typewriter or computer keyboard which
advances the carriage or curser to the next (preset) tab position; --
used especially to type or print text or numbers in columns.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tabacco</ent>⟦br⟧
